	(13713,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_1_position','Co-Chair Vantage Point Capital Partners'),
	(13714,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_1_position','field_533c6ddeeba9f'),
	(13715,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_1_bio','Richard Harroch joined VantagePoint in 2003 from Orrick, Herrington & Sutcliffe LLP, bringing with him an extensive body of transactional and business expertise. He is a successful entrepreneur, founder and Chairman of two companies: LawCommerce.com (sold to LexisNexis) and Allbusiness.com (sold to Dun and Bradstreet.)'),
	(13716,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_1_bio','field_533c6de5ebaa0'),
	(13717,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_2_name','Michael Barber'),
	(13718,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_2_name','field_533c6dd3eba9e'),
	(13719,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_2_position','Vice President, healthymagination GE Corporate'),
	(13720,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_2_position','field_533c6ddeeba9f'),
	(13721,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_2_bio','Michael Barber is a GE Officer and the VP of GE’s business strategy on global health for the corporation. The healthymagination charter is to improve the quality of care by 15% or more, to reduce the cost of procedures and processes through the appropriate use of GE technologies and services by 15% and to increase the access to essential technologies and services essential to health by 15%.'),
	(13722,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_2_bio','field_533c6de5ebaa0'),
	(13723,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_3_name','Kevin Brown'),
	(13724,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_3_name','field_533c6dd3eba9e'),
	(13725,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_3_position','General Partner Reed Elsevier Ventures'),
	(13726,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_3_position','field_533c6ddeeba9f'),
	(13727,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_3_bio','Kevin Brown has been involved in early stage technology & venture capital since the late nineties, first as an entrepreneur & then as an investor. He was a founding partner of Reed Elsevier Ventures in 2000 & has specialised in digital media, Internet and large scale data & technology investments since then.'),
	(13728,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_3_bio','field_533c6de5ebaa0'),
	(13729,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_4_name','Richard H. Carmona, MD, MPH'),
	(13730,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_4_name','field_533c6dd3eba9e'),
	(13731,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_4_position','FACS 17th Surgeon General of the United States (2002-2006)'),
	(13732,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_4_position','field_533c6ddeeba9f'),
	(13733,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_4_bio','In 2002, Dr. Carmona was nominated by the president and unanimously confirmed by the United States Senate to become the 17th Surgeon General of the United States. He is president of the non-profit Canyon Ranch Institute and Distinguished Professor at the Zuckerman College of Public Health at the University of Arizona.'),
	(13734,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_4_bio','field_533c6de5ebaa0'),
	(13735,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_5_name','Paul T. Sheils'),
	(13736,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_5_name','field_533c6dd3eba9e'),
	(13737,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_5_position','Managing Director Ansley Capital Group'),
	(13738,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_5_position','field_533c6ddeeba9f'),
	(13739,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_5_bio','Prior to joining The Ansley Capital Group, Paul Sheils was President & CEO of DocSite, LLC, an award-winning healthcare quality improvement and performance management company. He was also Founder and Managing Partner of Silverado Health Partners, LLC, a digital health management consulting firm, whose clients included GE Healthcare, J&J, UnitedHealth Group, and Hearst Digital Media.'),
	(13740,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_5_bio','field_533c6de5ebaa0'),
	(13741,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_6_name','Jim Warner'),
	(13742,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_6_name','field_533c6dd3eba9e'),
	(13743,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_6_position',''),
	(13744,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_6_position','field_533c6ddeeba9f'),
	(13745,482,'about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_6_bio','Jim Warner has a long and successful career as a leader in digital marketing and media. Most recently, he was at Avenue A|Razorfish and its parent company, aQuantive, where he advised a number of Fortune 500 companies including Capital One, Verizon and Starwood Hotels, on digital marketing, advertising and web strategy.'),
	(13746,482,'_about_us_page_content_1_directors_buckets_6_bio','field_533c6de5ebaa0'),
