of sites like Pinterest and Instagram. Even on Facebook, 300 million photos are uploaded (per day!) and posts with images average 84% higher CTR than just text.</li>\r\n	<li><strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">VIDEOS ARE HOT.</span></strong> Videos are a powerful tool in the social media marketing toolbox hierarchy. Apart from being the second largest search engine, YouTube accounts for 100 hours of video uploaded <em>every hour</em>.</li>\r\n	<li><strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">GOOGLE PLUS = GOOD SEO.</span></strong> As Google is making the Web a more personalized experience, from social to search, Google+ continues to rapidly grow.  With 300 million active users, G+ has quickly outpaced Twitter to become the second biggest social network behind Facebook.</li>\r\n	<li><strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">MOBILE (STILL) MATTERS.</span> </strong>Facebook mobile is the largest source of social traffic. And Pinterest (the second largest social referral network) mobile users account for more than 3/4 of total usage. (About 46% of Healthline.com\'s unique visitors viewed content exclusively from their mobile device.)</li>\r\n</ol>','Top Five Social Trends for 2014','','inherit','open','open','','124-revision-v1','','','2014-02-06 22:45:26','2014-02-06 22:45:26','',124,'http://corp-stage.healthline.com/blog/124-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(127,4,'2014-02-14 10:30:14','2014-02-14 10:30:14','Healthcare brands looking to make connections with contextually relevant audiences really have to be thinking about mobile. Everything we know today points to one simple fact: <strong>if your brand isn\'t on mobile, you\'re not on the Internet.</strong><!--more-->\r\n\r\nPharmaceutical marketers, in particular, need to confront radical changes in consumer health research behavior. Consider the following facts:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Eight of the top ten health information publishers see more than 30% of unique visitors who are mobile-only.</li>\r\n	<li>On Healthline.com, 46% of unique visitors view content exclusively from their mobile device, not from a desktop or laptop.</li>\r\n	<li>79% of traffic to Healthline.com\'s symptom checker is mobile, the beginning of treatment journey is through mobile.<a dir=\"ltr\" href=\"https://twitter.com/Kopportunity\">\r\n</a></li>\r\n	<li>Pharma brand names over index on mobile, condition treatment information does not.</li>\r\n	<li>The right way to engage with mobile is with content, not with banner ads.</li>\r\n	<li>If you do use banner ads, use non-flash creative as part of the media mix.  Thirty percent of mobile queries come from devices that are not Flash-enabled, reinforcing the need for creative developed outside of Flash.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/why-mobile-matters-advertisers.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-137 alignleft\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://corp.healthline.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/why-mobile-matters-advertisers.png\" width=\"250\" height=\"250\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe Healthline Media Group works with leading pharmaceutical and other brands to develop and deliver digital <a title=\"Healthline Marketing Solutions\" href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/solutions/marketing/\">marketing solutions</a> that engage consumers and deliver brand lift every day. Through this experience, we\'ve learned what