	(157,4,'2014-02-14 15:44:04','2014-02-14 15:44:04','It\'s snowing outside but social is on fire! I just got back to work from the <a href=\"http://www.iirusa.com/epharmasummit/welcome.xml\">ePharma</a> conference (a digital marketing event for the pharmaceutical industry) and was shocked and excited by all the social talk.  Almost every speaker and panel mentioned social. Clearly, its because marketers interested in creating connections and relationships with consumers need to be leaning into social. Here are a few tips and trends to watch and utilize to help you reach those hand-raisers.<!--more-->\n\nPeople use Facebook, and other social platforms to connect with others about what\'s on their minds, sometimes it\'s their condition, but other times they just want to connect with people like them.  Based on our experience with creating condition-specific communities that provide these contextual connections, our content team then they did some hard-core listening.  They just listened. It\'s simple but many companies miss this key best practice. We listened to what the communities brought forward, what questions they asked, what answers they gave, what they \"liked\".  From there we came up with the Top 5 Trends to Watch in 2014.\n<ol>\n	<li><strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">CONTENT IS STILL KING</span>.</strong> Creating remarkable content is the most cost-effective way to improve engagement on social media, attract new followers, and build organic traffic.</li>\n	<li><strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">IMAGE-CENTRICITY IS KEY.</span></strong> People like pictures, which accounts for the rise of sites like Pinterest and Instagram. Even on Facebook, 300 million photos are uploaded (per day!) and posts with images average 84% higher CTR than just text.</li>\n	<li><strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">VIDEOS ARE HOT.</span></strong> Videos are a powerful tool in the social media marketing toolbox hierarchy. Apart from being the second largest search engine, YouTube accounts for 100 hours of video uploaded <em>every hour</em>.</li>\n	<li><strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">GOOGLE PLUS = GOOD SEO.</span></strong> As Google is making the Web a more personalized experience, from social to search, Google+ continues to rapidly grow.  With 300 million active users, G+ has quickly outpaced Twitter to become the second biggest social network behind Facebook.</li>\n	<li><strong><span style=\"color: #800080;\">MOBILE (STILL) MATTERS.</span> </strong>Facebook mobile is the largest source of social traffic. And Pinterest (the second largest social referral network) mobile users account for more than 3/4 of total usage. (About 46% of Healthline.com\'s unique visitors viewed content exclusively from their mobile device.)</li>\n</ol>\n<a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/corporate-blog-img01.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-161 alignleft\" alt=\"Social and socially-inspired content\" src=\"http://corp.healthline.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/corporate-blog-img01-300x300.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>Our mission at Healthline is to make the people of the world healthier through the power of information. As part of that commitment, Healthline creates highly engaging and informative visual content, building and inspiring condition-specific communities across Facebook, Twitter and other social networks.\n\n<strong>What makes us experts? </strong>\nHealthline has more than <a title=\"Facebook.com/HealthlineNetworks\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/healthlinenetworks\" target=\"_blank\">250,000 fans</a> and 11 condition specific communities on Facebook, including <a title=\"Facebook.com/LivingWithMultipleSclerosisHealthline\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/LivingWithMultipleSclerosisHealthline\" target=\"_blank\">multiple sclerosis</a>, <a title=\"Healthline Crohn\'s Facebook Community\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/CrohnsDiseaseHealthline\" target=\"_blank\">Crohn\'s</a>, <a title=\"Healthline HIV Community on Facebook\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/TheNewFaceofHIV\" target=\"_blank\">HIV</a> and <a title=\"Healthline Facebook Bipolar Community\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/Living-with-Bipolar-Disorder-Healthline/283614231695971\" target=\"_blank\">bipolar</a>. On <a title=\"+Healthline\" href=\"https://plus.google.com/+healthline/posts\" target=\"_blank\">Google+</a>, we have 144,000 followers (more than two other health information sites that shall go unnamed <em>combined</em>!)\n\nI\'m getting buried by the snowstorm on the east coast, and I\'ve let all my friends know via Facebook, Twitter and Instagram, because social is on fire - and I need a little warmth.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWant more Healthline Media Group insights and news? Follow us on Twitter: <a href=\"https://twitter.com/HealthlineAdLab\">@HealthlineAdLab</a>','Top Five Social Trends for 2014','','inherit','open','open','','124-autosave-v1','','','2014-02-14 15:44:04','2014-02-14 15:44:04','',124,'http://corp.healthline.com/blog/124-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
