	(182,4,'2014-03-20 12:00:19','2014-03-20 19:00:19','&nbsp;\n\nThe diagnosis of a disease or condition is a serious and scary thing to face. Sometimes, this can leave people feeling alone. But they need to know that they’re not alone. They need to hear “You’ve Got This.”\n\n<b>What It Is:</b>\n\nThe “You’ve Got This” program illuminates how social provides meaningful value to the health-seeking Internet user. “You’ve Got This” is a powerful <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/about-us/press-releases/healthline-launches-new-public-service-initiative-with-the-national-ms-society/\">public service initiative</a> that gives hope to individuals recently diagnosed with a condition.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWe launched our first “You’ve Got This” program in August 2013. The <a href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/hiv-aids/youve-got-this\">“You’ve Got This” HIV</a> program gained lots of social buzz. After overwhelmingly positive feedback with patients and advocates alike, as well as major news media pick up, we followed up with a <a href=\"http://www.healthline.com/health/multiple-sclerosis/youve-got-this\">“You’ve Got This” MS</a>, and we are actively building a Bipolar version too.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>Sharing Safe Social With Rx and Health Advertisers:</b>\n\nHealthline’s had a lot of success in social (as a publisher) and has increasingly been able to bring pharma advertisers into those moments of connection. Instead of trying to push pharma into the conversations, we pull out the conversations happening in social. Our editors then curate and package this video content within our site. Advertisers have the opportunity to sponsor these safe, socially inspired video programs, aligning with community influencers and supportive patient stories.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>How It Works:</b><b></b>\n\nHealthline’s condition-specific <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/LivingWithMultipleSclerosisHealthline\">Facebook pages</a> feature a call out, asking those living with the condition to send in a video providing advice to someone recently diagnosed. Healthline curates the submitted videos and posts them to our website. We then share the videos on Facebook and spread the word back to the community.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>Why It Works:</b>\n\nPeople have amazing stories to tell. Content curating bubbles up <a href=\"http://corp-stage.healthline.com/blog/top-five-social-trends-for-2014/\">remarkable content,</a> and social provides a megaphone to share it. Most importantly, the “You’ve Got This” videos provided hope. Newly diagnosed patients and sufferers want to to feel they are not alone, and want to hear “You’ve Got This’.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWant more Healthline Media Group insights and news? Follow us on Twitter: <a href=\"https://twitter.com/HealthlineAdLab\">@HealthlineAdLab</a>','Social Breakthroug:  Welcoming Pharma Advertisers to Socially Inspired Video Content','','trash','open','open','','social-breakthroug-welcoming-pharma-advertisers-to-socially-inspired-video-content','','','2014-03-20 12:29:41','2014-03-20 19:29:41','',0,'http://corp.healthline.com/blog/?p=182',0,'post','',0),
