en curate and package this video content within our site. Advertisers have the opportunity to sponsor these safe, socially inspired video programs, aligning with community influencers and supportive patient stories.\r\n\r\n<b style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\">How It Works:</b>\r\n\r\nHealthline’s condition-specific <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/LivingWithMultipleSclerosisHealthline\">Facebook pages</a> feature a call out, asking those living with the condition to send in a video providing advice to someone recently diagnosed. Healthline curates the submitted videos and posts them to our website. We then share the videos on Facebook and spread the word back to the community.\r\n\r\n<b style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\">Why It Works:</b>\r\n\r\nPeople have amazing stories to tell. Content curation bubbles up <a href=\"http://corp.healthline.com/blog/top-five-social-trends-for-2014/\" target=\"_blank\">remarkable content,</a> and social provides a megaphone to share it. Most importantly, the “You’ve Got This” videos provided hope. Newly diagnosed patients and sufferers want to to feel they are not alone, and want to hear “You’ve Got This’.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\">Want more Healthline Media Group insights and news? Follow us on Twitter: </span><a style=\"font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5em;\" href=\"https://twitter.com/HealthlineAdLab\" target=\"_blank\">@HealthlineAdLab</a>','Welcoming Pharma Advertisers to Socially Inspired Video Content','','publish','open','open','','welcoming-pharma-advertisers-to-socially-inspired-video-content','','','2014-04-02 11:47:30','2014-04-02 18:47:30','',0,'http://corp.healthline.com/blog/?p=183',0,'post','',0),
